flowRoot.flowPara: is the dead core of a massive star
Release Gravitational Waves and make Gold!
At the end of its life, the core runs out of fuel and collapses under its own weight.
And the outer layers are ejected in a Supernova explosion
The collapsed core thus turns into a Neutron star
The pressure is such that protons and electrons are squashed together to make neutrons!
The immense pressure that caused protons and electrons to merge and form neutrons helps stabalise large nuclei with an excess of neutron that would never exist on Earth!
Lattice of iron nuclei with electrons free flowing in between. It's incredibly smooth! With a depth ~500 meters, bumps cannot be greater than 5mm.
In the outer core, the pressure is such that most nuclei have disolved and only neutrons remain. They form a special phase of matter called "Nuclear Pasta"
No-one knows what is truely at the center of a Neutron Star! The neutrons might desolve, leaving only quarks. Or could it even harbour Strange Matter?!
